      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nThis patch totally breaks my local node DNE setup (Easy to trigger: MDSCOUNT=2 sh llmount.sh cannot complete).\nConflict is apparently with http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/13786/27\n\nIn fact I just rejected that 13786 change, but there is some contention about the correct approach here, so I am holding on this one too for now.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "13aa9f28759698173f8c14dea233f16f87e28005",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 163,
        "name": "Gregoire Pichon",
        "email": "gregoire.pichon@eviden.com",
        "username": "pichong"
      },
      "date": "2015-06-24 13:24:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nOleg,\n\nI don't understand how your local node setup can be broken because of this patch. My local test configuration includes 2 MDT targets and it works.\n\nRegarding potential conflict with patch #13786, it's not planned to activate multislot feature for MDT-MDT connections. Therefore the last_xid embedded in the message will not be used by multislot server code for exports representing MDT clients (in out_handle() for example).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "bf978d6c7585319e99cf800abb6ab203124a510c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 163,
        "name": "Gregoire Pichon",
        "email": "gregoire.pichon@eviden.com",
        "username": "pichong"
      },
      "date": "2015-06-25 15:16:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nOleg,\n\nI agree there is an issue when adding this patch on top of patch #13786. I have reproduced the problem and I am currently investigating.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "f5dc13a43d2b11eeebdb94bf8942da44d5d60b6a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 163,
        "name": "Gregoire Pichon",
        "email": "gregoire.pichon@eviden.com",
        "username": "pichong"
      },
      "date": "2015-06-25 15:39:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nThis patch postpones the point where the request xid is assigned into ptlrpc_send_new_req() routine so that it can atomically assign xid and put the request to the sending list.\n\nUnfortunately, the patch #13786 stores the request xid in the out_update_header field of the message in osp_pre_update_req(). So with this patch it stores a 0 xid.\n\nI need to talk with Wang Di to see what solution can be found.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "26f4c99193e45cb55700f2cae601e72a914f7fcd",
